              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:σάλπιγξ&lt;SDBG:σάλπιγξ:000000&gt;}[a] trumpet, {D:6.89}) to produce sound with a trumpet</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to play the trumpet</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is possible, of course, in {S:04000600200012} to interpret σαλπίζω as a type of causative and thus to say ‘to cause someone to blow the trumpet’ or ‘to have the trumpet blown.’</Comments>
